{"id":"jabesh","term":"Jabesh","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Dry. (1.) For Jabesh-Gilead (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 11:3\">1 Sam. 11:3</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 11:9\">9</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 11:10\">10</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) The father of Shallum (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 15:10\">2 Kings 15:10</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 15:13\">13</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Kings 15:14\">14</a>), who usurped the throne of Israel on the death of Zachariah.</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Samuel 11:3","1 Samuel 11:9","1 Samuel 11:10","2 Kings 15:10","2 Kings 15:13","2 Kings 15:14"]}